23/11/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- The government has released military aid to six East European countries -- Bulgaria, Estonia, Lithuania, Latvia, Slovakia and Slovenia. The aid had been frozen because of the countries' refusal to sign bilateral agreements with the United States concerning the International Criminal Court. According to a statement by President George W. Bush, the decision was made to provide military assistance to "specific projects . needed to support the process of integration of these countries into NATO" and to support the campaigns in Iraq and Afghanistan. (AFP, BNT, bTV - 22/11/03)
